'''Ayoub Mohamed Al-Oui''' ({{Langx|ar|أيوب علوي‎}}; born 11 March 2005) is a Qatari professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[center-back]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]] and [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Club career==
A youth product of [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]], Al-Oui emerged as the team starter in the [[2025–26 Qatar Stars League|2025–26 season]] and played an important role helping the team win the [[2026 Amir of Qatar Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://alarab.qa/article/08/05/2026/%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%A9-%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%86%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%82-%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%A4%D9%83%D8%AF-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D8%A3%D8%BA%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%A4%D9%88%D8%B3-%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%B5%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B9%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%B6|title=جماهير الغرافة ستصنع الفارق.. أيوب علوي يؤكد "للعرب": أغلى الكؤوس فرصتنا الكبرى للتعويض|date=8 May 2026|publisher=Al Arab|language=ar}}</ref> Therefore, he was named the Best U-23 Player of the Season in the Qatar Stars League.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://staddoha.com/%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%85-%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AB%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%8B-%D9%88%D9%85%D9%82/|title=أيوب العلوي : الموسم كان استثنائياً ومقبلون على تحديات كبيرة |date=11 May 2026|publisher=Stad Doha|language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.al-watan.com/article/233815/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%A3%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%88%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AD%D9%86%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AB%D9%82%D8%A9|title=أيوب العلوي: تمنحني الثقـــة|date=12 May 2026|publisher=Al Watan|language=ar}}</ref>

==International career==
On 8 October 2025, Al-Oui made his international debut with [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC fourth round|2026 World Cup qualifiers]] game against [[Oman national football team|Oman]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dohanews.co/qatars-hopes-of-starting-world-cup-qualifiers-on-a-high-put-off-by-oman/|title=Qatar's hopes of starting World Cup qualifiers on a high put off by Oman|date=8 October 2025|publisher=Doha News}}</ref> Later in the year, he featured at the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.qfa.qa/en/news/lopetegui-finalizes-23-man-squad-for-fifa-arab-cup|title=Lopetegui Finalizes 23-Man Squad for FIFA Arab Cup|publisher=[[Qatar Football Association]]|date=24 November 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in Qatar, Al-Oui is of Tunisian descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://assarih.com/%D8%AD%D9%82%D9%8A%D9%82%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%B3-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7/|title=حقيقة تجنيس لاعبين تونسيين جديدين في المنتخب القطري الأول..|publisher=assarih|date=13 October 2025|language=ar}}</ref>

